Reka is an Emacs-based window manager for wayland. It is based on river.

https://codeberg.org/tazjin/reka

=== Q&A ===

==== Keybindings ====
Is there a way I can bind something globally so its passed through to emacs regardless of if its a reka window or a regular buffer? -- for brightness setting or something for example

basically you call (reka-push-intercept-prefix "s-d") for example, and then s-d becomes a key that is always sent to emacs

